Another cauſe of unthankfulneſſe is envy, then which there can hardly be a greater violation of the charity we owe to our neighbour: it is a fretfull, ſullen, dogged, and ſnarling vice, rottenneſſe unto the bones ſaith Solomon, Prov. 14 30. And this baſe and unworthy ſin doth alwayes produce ingratitude. The envious man undervalueth all that he hath, becauſe he ſuppoſeth it to be ſhort of what others have. He that hath an evill eye, a repyning heart, becauſe God is good to others ſlights Gods goodnes to himſelf, and repays it with nothing, but diſcontent, and murmuring;
